DarkOS network support
======================

Autostart:
- darkinit starts /usr/bin/network-up during boot.
- network-up loads common wired, virtual, USB Ethernet, and Wi-Fi modules.
- DHCP uses dhcpcd.
- /etc/resolv.conf is backed by writable /run/resolv.conf during boot.

Commands:
- help network
- network-status
- network-up
- network-up eth0
- ip addr
- ip route
- ping -c 3 alpine.org

Common wired and virtual modules:
- e100/e1000/e1000e/igb/igc/ixgbe
- r8169/8139too/8139cp
- tg3/b44/bnx2/bnx2x/bnxt_en
- atlantic/alx/atl1/atl1c/atl1e/atl2
- virtio_net/vmxnet3/hv_netvsc/ena/gve
- pcnet32/ne2k_pci/forcedeth

USB Ethernet modules:
- usbnet/cdc_ether/cdc_ncm/cdc_eem/cdc_mbim/rndis_host
- asix/ax88179_178a/dm9601/pegasus/r8152

Wi-Fi userspace:
- wpa_supplicant
- wireless-tools

Bundled firmware focuses on common wired NICs and common Realtek, Atheros,
Broadcom, MediaTek, and Intel Wi-Fi families.
